or knock that glass of water over?

767
00:50:33,663 --> 00:50:35,799
Well, if He did that, you wouldn't need

768
00:50:35,866 --> 00:50:38,135
much in the way of faith, would you?

769
00:50:38,201 --> 00:50:39,603
Why is it always about faith?

770
00:50:39,669 --> 00:50:42,139
That's what my wife used to say. Faith, faith, faith.

771
00:50:42,205 --> 00:50:45,409
It's all about faith. What about proof?

772
00:50:45,475 --> 00:50:47,878
It's not all faith, Thorold. Far from it.

773
00:50:47,944 --> 00:50:51,281
I mean, God says all you need is faith the size of a grain

774
00:50:51,348 --> 00:50:55,385
of mustard seed. He'll do the rest.

775
00:50:55,452 --> 00:50:59,689
But I want some proof. Some real proof. That's what I want.

776
00:50:59,756 --> 00:51:03,727
No proof is enough if the heart's not ready.

777
00:51:03,794 --> 00:51:08,365
What's that supposed to mean?

778
00:51:08,432 --> 00:51:11,701
It just means that whatever God may do,

779
00:51:11,768 --> 00:51:14,538
you won't believe it was Him anyway.

780
00:51:14,604 --> 00:51:19,443
You'll always manage to find another explanation.

781
00:51:21,645 --> 00:51:23,480
Another explanation.

782
00:51:25,248 --> 00:51:26,716
Well, I have an explanation.

783
00:51:28,251 --> 00:51:30,654
How's this for an explanation? There is no God.

784
00:51:31,988 --> 00:51:36,893
I wanna see Him. I wanna see it. I wanna see this thing,

785
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:40,597
this thing you call God. I wanna see some real proof.

786
00:51:40,664 --> 00:51:43,467
Knock over this glass of water, God. Knock over this

787
00:51:43,533 --> 00:51:45,669
little glass of water right now, and I'll be a believer.

788
00:51:45,735 --> 00:51:46,870
Come on!

789
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:48,405
Come on, God, make a believer outta me!

790
00:51:48,472 --> 00:51:50,941
You couldn't save my mother from cancer when I was a kid,

791
00:51:51,007 --> 00:51:52,409
and you sure as hell couldn't save my family from vanishing,

792
00:51:52,476 --> 00:51:55,278
so why don't you just knock over this little glass

793
00:51:55,345 --> 00:51:56,947
of water, and make a believer outta me!

794
00:51:57,013 --> 00:52:00,817
How 'bout it, God? Make a believer outta me! Huh?

795
00:52:00,884 --> 00:52:02,886
I guess He's not up to the challenge today, Helen.

796
00:52:02,953 --> 00:52:07,357
Looks to me like Macalusso's the only one around here pullin' off miracles.

797
00:52:07,424 --> 00:52:08,525
(bumping table)

798
00:52:08,592 --> 00:52:12,529
(glass rattling on floor)

799
00:52:30,013 --> 00:52:33,583
I'm not looking for God.

800
00:52:33,650 --> 00:52:37,888
I'm just looking for my family.

801
00:52:47,531 --> 00:52:49,733
Wendy...

802
00:52:51,801 --> 00:52:56,806
You know what, Cindy? I wish this were the same old program I already had.

803
00:52:56,873 --> 00:52:58,275
Why?

804
00:52:58,341 --> 00:53:01,278
'Cause then maybe I'd get to take a peek at you in a bikini.

805
00:53:01,344 --> 00:53:02,812
For heaven's sakes!

806
00:53:02,879 --> 00:53:04,948
Talk about your Day of Wonders, huh?

807
00:53:05,015 --> 00:53:06,416
Ruff!

808
00:53:06,483 --> 00:53:08,385
(howling)

809
00:53:08,451 --> 00:53:09,853
You're terrible.

810
00:53:11,454 --> 00:53:12,489
Hey.

811
00:53:19,996 --> 00:53:23,300
Right now, I'd give anything in the world to see

812
00:53:23,366 --> 00:53:29,573
Wendy and my little Maggie. For just a minute.

813
00:53:29,639 --> 00:53:31,975
What would you tell them?

814
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:36,012
That I love them.

815
00:53:36,079 --> 00:53:41,952
Sounds to me like you've pretty much figured out

816
00:53:42,018 --> 00:53:45,956
what's going on in this world, then.

817
00:53:46,022 --> 00:53:48,458
What are you talking about?

818
00:53:48,525 --> 00:53:51,461
I'm talking about God.

819
00:53:51,528 --> 00:53:57,367
Think about it. Just like Maggie is your creation,

820
00:53:57,434 --> 00:54:00,937
we're a part of God's creation.

821
00:54:01,004 --> 00:54:03,473
Helen...

822
00:54:03,540 --> 00:54:07,377
Thorold, think about Macalusso.

823
00:54:07,444 --> 00:54:10,547
I mean, he claims to be our creator.

824
00:54:10,614 --> 00:54:14,751
But at the heart of it, his message isn't about love it all.

825
00:54:14,818 --> 00:54:20,924
It's, it's about power. And selfishness.

826
00:54:20,991 --> 00:54:23,927
It's about having whatever you want,

827
00:54:23,994 --> 00:54:27,664
regardless of the consequences to anyone else.

828
00:54:27,731 --> 00:54:31,601
I mean, can you imagine sitting down and

829
00:54:31,668 --> 00:54:36,506
telling Maggie that in the name of success,

830
00:54:36,573 --> 00:54:40,777
she should kill anyone who stands in the way of her dreams?

831
00:54:40,844 --> 00:54:46,750
Isn't that exactly what Macalusso is telling the world?

832
00:54:46,816 --> 00:54:52,656
I'm telling you, Thorold.

833
00:54:52,722 --> 00:54:59,696
It's the same lie the serpent told Eve in the Garden of Eden.

834
00:54:59,763 --> 00:55:02,732
Come on, Eve. Eat the fruit.

835
00:55:02,799 --> 00:55:07,070
It won't hurt you. Look how good it looks.

836
00:55:07,137 --> 00:55:10,507
You know you want to.

837
00:55:10,573 --> 00:55:15,478
God's just afraid that if you eat it, you'll be just like Him.

838
00:55:17,113 --> 00:55:20,717
And what was your God doing when all this was happening?

839
00:55:21,918 --> 00:55:23,953
Just sitting there powerless?

840
00:55:24,020 --> 00:55:35,031
Oh, no. He wasn't just sitting there. Far from it.

841
00:55:38,768 --> 00:55:42,138
Now it's all in your hands.

842
00:55:42,205 --> 00:55:47,844
God doesn't want to win you with cheap tricks.

843
00:55:47,911 --> 00:55:50,814
He just wants you to reach into your heart and answer

844
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:56,419
one question: Do you believe in Him?

845
00:56:04,694 --> 00:56:08,665
It's time for you to decide what you believe, Thorold Stone.

846
00:56:27,717 --> 00:56:31,588
(computer beeping)

847
00:56:31,654 --> 00:56:32,856
Hey.

848
00:56:32,922 --> 00:56:35,158
You always carry a big stick.

849
00:56:35,225 --> 00:56:37,894
Only when there are new slobs in the house.

850
00:56:37,961 --> 00:56:39,863
Oh, great. Is this seat saved.

851
00:56:39,929 --> 00:56:42,532
No, but I'm sure you guys are prayin' for it.

852
00:56:42,599 --> 00:56:43,666
Oh...

853
00:56:43,733 --> 00:56:45,602
Hey Cindy, let me ask you something.

854
00:56:45,668 --> 00:56:47,771
Blind people always wear sunglasses, right?

855
00:56:47,837 --> 00:56:50,073
How come deaf people don't wear earmuffs?

856
00:56:50,140 --> 00:56:51,608
Willie, let me ask you something.

857
00:56:51,674 --> 00:56:54,110
Do men in wheelchairs complain when you leave the seat up?

858
00:56:54,177 --> 00:56:57,714
You, uh...you ever take those glasses off?

859
00:56:57,781 --> 00:56:59,549
Ah, only to drive.

860
00:56:59,616 --> 00:57:01,184
I'm trying to be serious, here.

861
00:57:01,251 --> 00:57:03,720
I've never seen you without 'em, that' all.

862
00:57:03,787 --> 00:57:05,555
Neither have I.

863
00:57:05,622 --> 00:57:10,560
Do you mind?

864
00:57:10,627 --> 00:57:15,165
Where are you?

865
00:57:26,009 --> 00:57:29,846
Wow.

866
00:57:29,913 --> 00:57:33,817
Well, I think you should definitely take them off more often.

867
00:57:33,883 --> 00:57:38,087
You're the most beautiful woman I've ever seen.

868
00:57:38,154 --> 00:57:42,959
Thanks...

869
00:57:43,026 --> 00:57:48,698
So, what makes a nice girl like you become a bible-thumper, anyway?

870
00:57:48,765 --> 00:57:50,700
Well, I was really an atheist, but you know,

871
00:57:50,767 --> 00:57:52,335
they didn't have enough holidays.

872
00:57:52,402 --> 00:57:55,038
Now, come on, I'm bein' serious, here.

873
00:57:55,104 --> 00:57:57,841
I mean, look at the way you people live.

874
00:57:57,907 --> 00:58:01,644
Hidin' out in this rathole, livin' every day in fear.

875
00:58:01,711 --> 00:58:04,681
You must really believe this stuff, huh?

876
00:58:04,747 --> 00:58:06,182
I'll tell you the truth, Willie,

877
00:58:06,249 --> 00:58:08,351
I really don't know what I believe.

878
00:58:08,418 --> 00:58:11,855
My parents used to drag me to church every Sunday.

879
00:58:11,921 --> 00:58:17,694
I would pray for eyesight. Mom and dad vanished and Jake

880
00:58:17,760 --> 00:58:22,765
here came to get me, well, what was I gonna do?

881
00:58:22,832 --> 00:58:26,769
I guess you could say I just came along for the ride.

882
00:58:26,836 --> 00:58:29,138
Aw, come on. Along for the ride?

883
00:58:29,205 --> 00:58:31,107
I mean, I watched you last night. I saw you out there

884
00:58:31,174 --> 00:58:33,610
prayin' and singin' with them.

885
00:58:33,676 --> 00:58:35,144
Please!

886
00:58:35,211 --> 00:58:36,346
Going to church makes you about as Christian

887
00:58:36,412 --> 00:58:39,716
as going to a pet store makes you a cat.

888
00:58:39,782 --> 00:58:46,356
You know? What about you, Willie? What's your story?

889
00:58:46,422 --> 00:58:47,891
The truth?

890
00:58:47,957 --> 00:58:49,792
No, lie.

891
00:58:49,859 --> 00:58:52,295
Well, I still believe Franco Mcalusso is who he

892
00:58:52,362 --> 00:58:55,965
says he is, the Messiah. And if I can just get to the

893
00:58:56,032 --> 00:59:01,037
bottom of this whole program mess, I can prove that.

894
00:59:01,104 --> 00:59:03,339
To the whole world.

895
00:59:04,841 --> 00:59:07,777
For the last time, Helen, I don't wanna hear about it!

896
00:59:07,844 --> 00:59:09,345
I've explained it to you so many times--

897
00:59:09,412 --> 00:59:11,314
Thorold!

898
00:59:11,381 --> 00:59:14,017
Oh, it's okay, guys! Wait, it's okay. We're all on the same side.

899
00:59:14,083 --> 00:59:15,985
We're all on the same side.

900
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:18,788
Ronnie, how did you do?

901
00:59:18,855 --> 00:59:21,357
A lot better than Selma Davis.

902
00:59:21,424 --> 00:59:23,126
What do you mean?

903
00:59:23,192 --> 00:59:26,863
I got this tape out of the security camera.

904
00:59:29,866 --> 00:59:31,601
What are you holding on to?

905
00:59:31,668 --> 00:59:34,804
Don't you see you've lost? You've lost! God's lost!

906
00:59:34,871 --> 00:59:37,206
Once you and every other Christian is dead or converted,

907
00:59:37,273 --> 00:59:39,142
He'll have no reason to return.

908
00:59:39,208 --> 00:59:40,209
He won't have anyone to come back for, and that's what the

909
00:59:40,276 --> 00:59:43,346
Day of Wonders is all about!

910
00:59:43,413 --> 00:59:44,948
You're gonna renounce Christ, or you're going to die!

911
00:59:45,014 --> 00:59:47,417
Prophecy will fail, and we will win.

912
00:59:47,483 --> 00:59:50,887
So save your life now. Renounce Him!

913
00:59:55,358 --> 00:59:59,295
So that's what the Day of Wonders is all about, huh?

914
00:59:59,362 --> 01:00:02,398
Killing people?

915
01:00:02,465 --> 01:00:07,070
How's he gonna do it? With some fancy computer game?

916
01:00:07,136 --> 01:00:09,138
What about all the people he vapourized? He didn't say

917
01:00:09,205 --> 01:00:12,275
anything about that. What's gonna happen to them.

918
01:00:12,342 --> 01:00:15,078
He didn't vapourize anybody, Thorold.

919
01:00:15,144 --> 01:00:18,715
God took them home. Your family's in heaven.

920
01:00:18,781 --> 01:00:20,583
(static)

921
01:00:20,650 --> 01:00:23,886
Special Agent Thorold Stone. I know you're listening.

922
01:00:23,953 --> 01:00:26,122
I just thought you might be interested in some special

923
01:00:26,189 --> 01:00:29,826
guests I have here, visiting me in my office.

924
01:00:29,892 --> 01:00:32,128
It took some doing to get them here, Stone.

925
01:00:32,195 --> 01:00:35,131
I hope you appreciate the effort.

926
01:00:35,198 --> 01:00:37,000
Please don't hurt us anymore!

927
01:00:37,066 --> 01:00:40,169
We don't know anything. I haven't seem him in months.

928
01:00:40,236 --> 01:00:43,873
Mommy, why doesn't daddy come and save us?

929
01:00:43,940 --> 01:00:45,742
I don't know, honey. I don't know.

930
01:00:45,808 --> 01:00:50,880
Shut up, both of you. Unless you want more of the same.

931
01:00:50,947 --> 01:00:55,318
Stone? You have one choice, and one choice only,

932
01:00:55,385 --> 01:00:58,821
so you'd better listen to me very carefully.

933
01:00:58,888 --> 01:01:02,191
I want to see you here, and O.N.E. headquarters

934
01:01:02,258 --> 01:01:05,995
by 2:00 a.m. with the disk. Have you got that?

935
01:01:06,062 --> 01:01:09,499
If you're not here by one second past two,

936
01:01:09,565 --> 01:01:11,868
then they'll be the first ones to discover

937
01:01:11,934 --> 01:01:14,971
what the Day of Wonders is all about.

938
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:22,845
Please don't hurt my daughter. She hasn't done anything. Please, you--

939
01:01:28,151 --> 01:01:30,186
Thorold? Thorold.

940
01:01:30,253 --> 01:01:32,955
You've got to listen to me, it's a trick.

941
01:01:33,022 --> 01:01:35,158
Parker doesn't have your family. It's a trick.

942
01:01:35,224 --> 01:01:38,528
No, that's my Wendy and my Maggie.

943
01:01:38,594 --> 01:01:42,165
No, listen to me. He's done it before and he's doing it again.

944
01:01:42,231 --> 01:01:48,337
No, it's okay. I'm not gonna take the disk to him.

945
01:01:48,404 --> 01:01:53,843
But tell me, what do I do?

946
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:58,347
I'll destroy it. I'll destroy the Day of Wonders.

947
01:01:58,414 --> 01:02:01,818
That's what I have to do. Will you help me?

948
01:02:01,884 --> 01:02:03,319
Thorold--

949
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:05,221
Please, I need your help.

950
01:02:05,288 --> 01:02:08,858
Please, will you help me.

951
01:02:08,925 --> 01:02:10,226
I know how we can stop it, Thorold.

952
01:02:10,293 --> 01:02:11,761
Willie-

953
01:02:11,828 --> 01:02:13,296
Listen, Cindy, I don't know what Macalusso had planned for

954
01:02:13,362 --> 01:02:15,932
the Day of Wonders, but Parker and his gang of dirtbags

955
01:02:15,998 --> 01:02:18,501
obviously have some very different ideas.

956
01:02:18,568 --> 01:02:21,971
Now look, the mainframe computer at the O.N.E. building

957
01:02:22,038 --> 01:02:24,140
is the hub for the entire system, right?

958
01:02:24,207 --> 01:02:28,544
If we could just upload a virus, that could infect every computer on the network.

959
01:02:28,611 --> 01:02:29,946
Meaning?

960
01:02:30,012 --> 01:02:33,015
Meaning that if it works, tomorrow afternoon when

961
01:02:33,082 --> 01:02:35,251
the whole world puts on those goggles,

962
01:02:35,318 --> 01:02:38,387
they won't see any more in there than Cindy sees out here.

963
01:02:38,454 --> 01:02:42,125
And without me, they won't be re-writin' it any time soon.

964
01:02:42,191 --> 01:02:44,494
But what about that line of encryption on the program?

965
01:02:44,560 --> 01:02:46,062
I mean, are you going to destroy the Day of Wonders

966
01:02:46,129 --> 01:02:47,563
before you even see what it is?

967
01:02:47,630 --> 01:02:49,031
No, the computer's still workin' on that,

968
01:02:49,098 --> 01:02:52,068
but I can guarantee you that that is not the answer.

969
01:02:52,135 --> 01:02:55,104
Yeah, well how do you know that?

970
01:02:55,171 --> 01:02:57,940
Thorold, remember that day we went walkin' on the beach?

971
01:02:58,007 --> 01:02:59,075
Yeah.

972
01:02:59,142 --> 01:03:00,343
Yeah, you remember that seashell?

973
01:03:00,409 --> 01:03:01,544
Yeah.

974
01:03:01,611 --> 01:03:02,411
Yeah, well that single seashell was made up of

975
01:03:02,478 --> 01:03:03,613
almost 4,000 lines of code.

976
01:03:03,679 --> 01:03:06,149
We're talkin' about one line, here.

977
01:03:06,215 --> 01:03:09,018
I'm telling you, whatever they have planned for the day of

978
01:03:09,085 --> 01:03:13,022
wonders, it's not on that disk. And at noon tomorrow,

979
01:03:13,089 --> 01:03:15,424
the whole world's gonna put on those glasses,

980
01:03:15,491 --> 01:03:18,594
and find themselves in the middle of who knows what.

981
01:03:18,661 --> 01:03:21,164
Yeah, well we don't have until noon tomorrow. So let's stop

982
01:03:21,230 --> 01:03:24,901
wastin' time talkin' about if, and start talkin' about how.

983
01:03:24,967 --> 01:03:26,369
I got a plan.

984
01:03:26,435 --> 01:03:28,437
Look, the O.N.E. cleaning staff comes in at around 11:30, right?

985
01:03:28,504 --> 01:03:32,909
I can access the security computer and get Thorold in there as a janitor.

986
01:03:32,975 --> 01:03:34,977
Oh yeah, right. Like they won't notice a new face.

987
01:03:35,044 --> 01:03:40,049
No way. That place is huge. About 5,000 people walk by that security desk every day.

988
01:03:40,116 --> 01:03:41,250
Well, let's do it.

989
01:03:41,317 --> 01:03:43,219
Are you going to be able to find the V.R. lab?

990
01:03:43,286 --> 01:03:44,420
Shouldn't be a problem as long as the

991
01:03:44,487 --> 01:03:45,688
files Willie pulled are complete.

992
01:03:45,755 --> 01:03:47,223
Now, the challenge is gonna be the alarms.

993
01:03:47,290 --> 01:03:49,692
This notepad contains all the info you're gonna need to

994
01:03:49,759 --> 01:03:51,260
deactivate the alarm system, but once you're inside

995
01:03:51,327 --> 01:03:52,795
you're gonna have to hurry.

996
01:03:52,862 --> 01:03:55,064
Now, if you come to a fork in the road, Thorold, take it.

997
01:03:55,131 --> 01:03:57,033
Oh Willie, everything's a joke to you.

998
01:03:57,099 --> 01:03:58,601
Thorold?

999
01:03:58,668 --> 01:04:01,204
Godspeed.

1000
01:04:01,270 --> 01:04:03,706
I told you, I don't believe in God.

1001
01:04:03,773 --> 01:04:06,709
It's okay.

1002
01:04:06,776 --> 01:04:10,146
He believes in you.

1003
01:04:13,049 --> 01:04:15,585
Man, I just... I don't know what else I can do.

1004
01:04:15,651 --> 01:04:19,689
There is just nothin' in there, Cindy.

1005
01:04:19,755 --> 01:04:22,458
I guess we'll just have to wait to hear from Thorold.

1006
01:04:22,525 --> 01:04:25,628
And this stupid line of code!

1007
01:04:25,695 --> 01:04:29,966
I mean, it's only one line. What can it possibly say?

1008
01:04:30,032 --> 01:04:33,502
Then why did they go through all this trouble to keep you out?

1009
01:04:33,569 --> 01:04:40,076
I guess I better call Thorold before he gets inside.

1010
01:04:40,142 --> 01:04:42,478
Thorold?

1011
01:04:42,545 --> 01:04:45,648
Yeah, here I am, I'm doin' fine.

1012
01:04:45,715 --> 01:04:47,984
I'm about three minutes out. How are you doin'?

1013
01:04:48,050 --> 01:04:49,518
