01:23:04,212 --> 01:23:09,317
(chuckling)

1269
01:23:09,384 --> 01:23:12,354
Oh, I was wrong about you.

1270
01:23:12,420 --> 01:23:17,625
I actually thought you were an alien.

1271
01:23:17,692 --> 01:23:21,229
Yes, I know.

1272
01:23:21,296 --> 01:23:26,501
But now you believe. Don't you?

1273
01:23:26,568 --> 01:23:29,137
Now I believe.

1274
01:23:33,208 --> 01:23:34,676
Hold it.

1275
01:23:36,144 --> 01:23:36,845
Oh Ronnie, I hope he hasn't put those goggles on yet.

1276
01:23:36,911 --> 01:23:38,513
Let's hope he hasn't.

1277
01:23:38,580 --> 01:23:39,681
Which way now?

1278
01:23:39,748 --> 01:23:41,216
This way.

1279
01:23:41,282 --> 01:23:46,121
Now all you have to do is give me your pledge of allegiance,

1280
01:23:46,187 --> 01:23:52,694
and everything you've ever dreamed of will be yours.

1281
01:23:52,761 --> 01:23:58,500
You're not about love at all, are you?

1282
01:23:58,566 --> 01:24:01,870
I would rather believe in a creator who would die for his

1283
01:24:01,936 --> 01:24:07,142
creation than have his creation die for him.

1284
01:24:07,208 --> 01:24:08,676
My son--

1285
01:24:08,743 --> 01:24:14,682
I am not your son, Satan.

1286
01:24:14,749 --> 01:24:20,321
And they are not my family.

1287
01:24:20,388 --> 01:24:26,561
I know where my family is, where they'll be safe from you for eternity.

1288
01:24:26,628 --> 01:24:31,466
So be it.

1289
01:24:31,533 --> 01:24:35,303
You've made your choice.

1290
01:24:35,370 --> 01:24:42,210
And now you will pay the price.

1291
01:24:42,277 --> 01:24:47,849
Not even your God can save you.

1292
01:24:47,916 --> 01:24:49,851
He already has.

1293
01:24:55,423 --> 01:24:59,627
(maniacal laughter)

1294
01:25:19,681 --> 01:25:22,183
(locks snapping shut)

1295
01:25:33,895 --> 01:25:35,864
So this is the Day of Wonders?

1296
01:25:35,930 --> 01:25:38,466
You make the world worship you or die.

1297
01:25:38,533 --> 01:25:41,402
I don't have to make them worship me.

1298
01:25:41,469 --> 01:25:43,705
They'll want to worship me.

1299
01:25:43,771 --> 01:25:47,342
And do you know why? Do you?

1300
01:25:47,408 --> 01:25:51,246
Because I give them everything that they want.

1301
01:25:51,312 --> 01:25:53,715
And just like Eve in the Garden of Eden,

1302
01:25:53,781 --> 01:25:57,552
they snap it up in a second. And those that don't,

1303
01:25:57,619 --> 01:26:02,624
well, they die. So either way, I win.

1304
01:26:02,690 --> 01:26:10,632
Pretty soon everything on this whole earth will be mine.

1305
01:26:10,698 --> 01:26:16,271
All of it will be mine.

1306
01:26:16,337 --> 01:26:21,009
And there's no reason for God to come back, now, is there?

1307
01:26:21,075 --> 01:26:26,047
I found out who you really are by saying no.

1308
01:26:26,114 --> 01:26:33,421
What about those who said yes? When do they find out?

1309
01:26:33,488 --> 01:26:36,391
Tomorrow.

1310
01:26:36,457 --> 01:26:40,295
But by then, it's going to be too late.

1311
01:26:40,361 --> 01:26:44,999
You see, once they give me the pledge of allegiance,

1312
01:26:45,066 --> 01:26:54,876
they will be mine for eternity. And those that aren't are dead.

1313
01:26:54,943 --> 01:27:00,915
It's a wonderful day, don't you think?

1314
01:27:00,982 --> 01:27:05,353
Lord, I didn't honour you with my life.

1315
01:27:05,420 --> 01:27:11,626
By your grace, may I do so in death.

1316
01:27:11,693 --> 01:27:15,730
Oh! Very touching.

1317
01:27:15,797 --> 01:27:21,002
Goodbye, Thorold Stone.

1318
01:27:25,073 --> 01:27:27,742
Thorold, are you okay?

1319
01:27:27,809 --> 01:27:31,379
Helen!

1320
01:27:31,446 --> 01:27:33,114
Everything really happened in there.

1321
01:27:33,181 --> 01:27:35,717
I know, I know. But I heard you make the right decision.

1322
01:27:35,783 --> 01:27:37,518
Oh...

1323
01:27:37,585 --> 01:27:41,489
Where's Willie?

1324
01:27:41,556 --> 01:27:43,791
He met Macalusso in there too.

1325
01:27:43,858 --> 01:27:45,693
He made the wrong decision.

1326
01:27:45,760 --> 01:27:48,496
He took the mark of the beast.

1327
01:27:48,563 --> 01:27:52,667
That's why he wanted me to put the goggles on.

1328
01:27:52,734 --> 01:27:55,870
Once you're inside, you either accept the mark or you die.

1329
01:27:55,937 --> 01:27:58,473
Yeah, either way you wouldn't be uploading that virus.

1330
01:27:58,539 --> 01:28:01,409
Well, they won't be far behind us, guys. Let's move.

1331
01:28:01,476 --> 01:28:06,447
All right. All right...

1332
01:28:06,514 --> 01:28:09,117
The first thing he's gonna do is check this console.

1333
01:28:09,183 --> 01:28:10,585
That's where I was supposed to upload the virus. There's gotta

1334
01:28:10,652 --> 01:28:13,454
be another computer that linked to the main network.

1335
01:28:13,521 --> 01:28:16,457
How about that one?

1336
01:28:27,568 --> 01:28:28,936
We're in.

1337
01:28:29,003 --> 01:28:31,839
(computer beeping)

1338
01:28:31,906 --> 01:28:33,041
How long is gonna take?

1339
01:28:33,107 --> 01:28:36,444
Hopefully no longer than we've got.

1340
01:28:36,511 --> 01:28:39,480
We've got no time. They're here.

1341
01:28:39,547 --> 01:28:41,549
Thorold!

1342
01:28:41,616 --> 01:28:45,053
Okay, okay, all right. Find me another black disk.

1343
01:28:45,119 --> 01:28:46,254
What?

1344
01:28:46,320 --> 01:28:48,089
Another black disk! Find another black disk!

1345
01:28:55,496 --> 01:28:57,065
Thorold, got one.

1346
01:28:57,131 --> 01:29:00,835
Spin that console around.

1347
01:29:04,939 --> 01:29:07,108
Hold it right there, my friend!

1348
01:29:07,175 --> 01:29:11,646
Looks like we got here just in time.

1349
01:29:11,713 --> 01:29:15,383
Well, what are you waiting for? Get the disk!

1350
01:29:17,218 --> 01:29:19,120
I'll take that.

1351
01:29:20,521 --> 01:29:25,827
What's the matter, stupid? Did all the big words confuse you?

1352
01:29:25,893 --> 01:29:29,764
Nice to see you.

1353
01:29:37,171 --> 01:29:38,740
Open the door.

1354
01:29:39,540 --> 01:29:41,409
(computer beeping)

1355
01:29:45,680 --> 01:29:46,514
What's the matter with the door?

1356
01:29:46,581 --> 01:29:48,282
I don't know why it's so slow.

1357
01:29:48,349 --> 01:29:50,985
All the access doors were a little slow on the way down here.

1358
01:29:51,052 --> 01:29:53,154
The boys upstairs must be running some big program on

1359
01:29:53,221 --> 01:29:55,256
the main computer system.

1360
01:29:55,323 --> 01:29:59,761
Three more guests for your little fireside prayer meeting.

1361
01:29:59,827 --> 01:30:03,131
The virus!

1362
01:30:03,197 --> 01:30:05,633
But before we turn up the heat,

1363
01:30:05,700 --> 01:30:09,504
I'm gonna give you all one last chance.

1364
01:30:09,570 --> 01:30:12,507
Renounce Him.

1365
01:30:12,573 --> 01:30:17,211
Let me tell you something, Mr. Parker.

1366
01:30:17,278 --> 01:30:21,716
The God we serve is with us.

1367
01:30:21,783 --> 01:30:27,221
And he is fully able to deliver us from this place. But even

1368
01:30:27,288 --> 01:30:33,928
if he doesn't, rest assured we will never serve Macalusso.

1369
01:30:33,995 --> 01:30:38,266
Nor worship his image or take his mark.

1370
01:30:38,332 --> 01:30:40,101
Ever.

1371
01:30:40,168 --> 01:30:41,602
Amen.

1372
01:30:46,307 --> 01:30:49,610
As you wish.

1373
01:30:55,850 --> 01:30:59,587
I'm glad the Lord has opened your eyes, son.

1374
01:30:59,654 --> 01:31:01,122
I'm sorry.

1375
01:31:01,189 --> 01:31:03,257
It's okay.

1376
01:31:03,324 --> 01:31:08,229
You're forgiven. We all are.

1377
01:31:08,296 --> 01:31:11,899
And if the end result is your soul,

1378
01:31:11,966 --> 01:31:18,773
then what we've been through is a small price to pay.

1379
01:31:18,840 --> 01:31:27,949
♪ Amazing grace how sweet the sound ♪

1380
01:31:28,015 --> 01:31:37,758
♪ that saved a wretch like me ♪

1381
01:31:37,825 --> 01:31:48,302
♪ I once was lost but now I'm found ♪

1382
01:31:48,369 --> 01:31:52,006
Let's see if they can sing and scream at the same time.

1383
01:31:52,073 --> 01:31:57,812
(roaring flames)

1384
01:31:57,879 --> 01:32:02,016
(door crashing open)

1385
01:32:02,083 --> 01:32:06,354
Cindy, get off of me! Look for the disk!

1386
01:32:06,420 --> 01:32:14,028
♪ was grace that taught my heart to fear ♪

1387
01:32:14,095 --> 01:32:18,833
Why are they still singing?

1388
01:32:18,900 --> 01:32:22,103
Why aren't they burning?

1389
01:32:22,169 --> 01:32:24,338
It's a black O.N.E. Disk!

1390
01:32:24,405 --> 01:32:25,907
But Willie, I can't read!

1391
01:32:25,973 --> 01:32:27,875
Just pop this! Pop this!

1392
01:32:27,942 --> 01:32:29,777
Pop any disk! Pop any disk!

1393
01:32:29,844 --> 01:32:33,047
They're not burning.

1394
01:32:33,114 --> 01:32:35,883
It's Him! He's protecting them!

1395
01:32:35,950 --> 01:32:38,019
Turn it up more! Now!

1396
01:32:38,085 --> 01:32:39,420
(flames roaring)

1397
01:32:39,487 --> 01:32:41,923
He can't do this. He can't do this!

1398
01:32:41,989 --> 01:32:42,990
Where is it?

1399
01:32:43,057 --> 01:32:44,191
It's not here!

1400
01:32:44,258 --> 01:32:45,326
It's gotta be here! It's gotta be here!

1401
01:32:45,393 --> 01:32:46,861
Where else? Where else would it be?

1402
01:32:46,928 --> 01:32:48,062
Right there.

1403
01:32:48,129 --> 01:32:51,866
(singing growing louder, flames roaring)

1404
01:32:51,933 --> 01:32:53,834
These souls are mine! They have to die!

1405
01:32:53,901 --> 01:32:55,703
Yes, yes...

1406
01:32:55,770 --> 01:32:56,370
Cindy...

1407
01:32:56,437 --> 01:32:56,971
What?

1408
01:32:57,038 --> 01:32:57,705
Wait a minute...

1409
01:32:57,772 --> 01:32:59,907
What, Willie? What?

1410
01:32:59,974 --> 01:33:02,209
Turn it up more! Turn it up more!

1411
01:33:02,276 --> 01:33:04,946
It's overloading. You'll burn down the whole building.

1412
01:33:05,012 --> 01:33:05,846
(gunshot)

1413
01:33:05,913 --> 01:33:07,715
No, no!

1414
01:33:08,749 --> 01:33:10,751
No! No!

1415
01:33:10,818 --> 01:33:13,821
This is impossible! No!

1416
01:33:13,888 --> 01:33:17,124
(singing, roaring flames)

1417
01:33:17,191 --> 01:33:21,262
This is our day! Our time!

1418
01:33:21,329 --> 01:33:23,130
No!

1419
01:33:23,197 --> 01:33:25,199
What? What?

1420
01:33:25,266 --> 01:33:30,371
(hail of gunfire)

1421
01:33:30,438 --> 01:33:33,207
All the way!

1422
01:33:33,274 --> 01:33:35,710
No...

1423
01:33:35,776 --> 01:33:36,744
What?

1424
01:33:36,811 --> 01:33:38,412
What, Willie, what?

1425
01:33:38,479 --> 01:33:42,850
Tell me! Tell me!

1426
01:33:42,917 --> 01:33:45,319
It's over, Cindy.

1427
01:33:45,386 --> 01:33:46,487
What?

1428
01:33:46,554 --> 01:33:47,722
It's over.

1429
01:33:47,788 --> 01:33:51,826
No-- NO!

1430
01:33:51,892 --> 01:33:54,729
I'll finish them myself.

1431
01:33:54,795 --> 01:33:57,231
(screaming)

1432
01:33:57,298 --> 01:34:03,070
♪ ...from when we first begun... ♪

1433
01:34:03,137 --> 01:34:05,873
Former WNN news anchor Helen Hannah has

1434
01:34:05,940 --> 01:34:08,809
apparently done it again. Authorities are scrambling

1435
01:34:08,876 --> 01:34:10,945
to make sense of what happened last night as

1436
01:34:11,012 --> 01:34:13,414
the O.N.E. headquarters burned to the ground.

1437
01:34:13,481 --> 01:34:15,816
However, there is no doubt that the much-anticipated

1438
01:34:15,883 --> 01:34:18,152
Day of Wonders project has been postponed.

1439
01:34:18,219 --> 01:34:20,021
(cheers, applause)

1440
01:34:20,087 --> 01:34:21,689
We've also learned that Miss Hannah escaped from the

1441
01:34:21,756 --> 01:34:25,292
O.N.E. Rehabilitation facility overnight. The Messiah had

1442
01:34:25,359 --> 01:34:28,863
this to say from Jerusalem just a few hours ago.

1443
01:34:28,929 --> 01:34:37,071
And yet another act of hatred and of selfishness.

1444
01:34:37,138 --> 01:34:45,179
The haters have stolen the Day of Wonders from us.

1445
01:34:45,246 --> 01:34:55,056
From the new and united world. But rest assured,

1446
01:34:55,122 --> 01:34:59,927
they will not prevail against us. We will double

1447
01:34:59,994 --> 01:35:05,232
our efforts of the followers of the deceiver, Jesus.

